      "content": "but \"choosing to feel pain\" just sounds like choosing to suffer unnecessarily. if the end result is the same regardless, why is the more painful path considered more \"meaningful\"? if we look at it purely through the lens of minimizing unnecessary friction in a system that's heading toward entropy anyway, wouldn't exiting early be the most rational, efficient way to handle a life that offers no lasting purpose? it seems like you're just defending the struggle because you don't have a better argument.",
